libipcmd implemented VCC IP Command Protocol which is defining a control channel for
IP based networks. The protocol is designed for in-vehicle communication, between 
IP-based ECUs.


* Design Concepts

--------------------------------                --------------------------------          
|          Application#1       |                |          Application#2       |
--------------------------------                --------------------------------
         |              |                              |                |
-------------------     |                       ------------------      |
| (IPCMD Service) | ----------------            | (IPCMD Service)| ----------------
| (IPCMD Server)  | |(IPCMD Client)|            | (IPCMD Server) | |(IPCMD Client)|
------------------- ----------------            ------------------ ----------------
         |              |                              |                |
         |(CHID#2)      |(CHID#2)                      |(CHID#2)        |(CHID#2)
         |              |                              |                |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
         |              |                              |                |
         ---------------      IP COMMAND BUS           -----------------
               |                                            |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
               ^                                            ^
               |                                            |
               |           (Transport for Channel#2)        |
               ----------------------------------------------
           (UDP/TCP Client)                              (UDP/TCP Server)
                                     or
           (UDP/TCP Server)                              (UDP/TCP Client)
